commit.message:
Allow consumers of ArelHelpers::QueryBuilder to chain on falsy return (#44)

* Allow consumers of ArelHelpers::QueryBuilder to chain on falsy return

If you want to optimally chain a number of queries it quickly becomes very noisy to wrap each execution in an if-statements and handle the various returns.

ArelHelpers::QueryBuilder is a nice way to avoid that but it can end up with a similar problem. Each query method defines needs to check the desired expression and then either add to the base query or return `reflect(query)`.

This commit adds a utility module that can be extended in the sub class of ArelHelpers::QueryBuilder. In that way it doesn’t modify ArelHelpers::QueryBuilder at all but proveds an additional opt-in behaviour that works well together with ArelHelpers::QueryBuilder.

Remove `has_rdoc` from gem specification (#41)

RubyGems 2.7.7 [deprecated the has_rdoc property][1] for gem
specifications. As such, loading this gem with a newer version of
RubyGems raises a warning that will eventually be an error. It would be
nice to nip this in the bud.

[1]: https://github.com/ruby/ruby/commit/c6da9cadb346cc1d250c7ed6d8fd33c62a11030e#diff-05477d38d75c98664b0e7dec6eb73b45R2025
